(122, 1, '2016-12-18 18:24:55', '2016-12-18 18:24:55', 'Itâs easy for visitors to sign in with Envoy. Theyâll walk up to your front desk and see your logo or branding right on the iPad welcome screen. Then, theyâll just tap to sign in.\r\n\r\nTheyâll then be presented with the sign-in fields. These are fully customizable by the Envoy admin, and can be set to required or optional. During this stage, the visitor can specify who theyâre meeting with by filling in the host field. When they do so, Envoy will send an automatic host notification to the employee, letting them know their visitor has arrived.\r\n\r\nNext, depending on the customizations preferred by the company, the visitor might also sign an NDA directly on the iPad, have their visitor photo taken with the iPadâs front-facing camera, see a custom message or watch a video.\r\n\r\nEnvoy can also be connected to the compatible Brother QL-720NW printer to automatically print a badge every time a visitor arrives', 'What is Envoy?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'what-is-envoy', '', '', '2016-12-18 18:24:55', '2016-12-18 18:24:55', '', 0, 'http://chameleoninfosoft.com/helpdesk/?post_type=help_articles&#038;p=122', 0, 'help_articles', '', 0),
(123, 1, '2016-12-18 18:25:59', '2016-12-18 18:25:59', 'Envoy isnât just great for you and your teamâit simplifies sign-in for your visitors, too. Instead of scrambling with paperwork, theyâll sign in directly on your iPad.\r\n\r\nYou have full control over what sign-in steps visitors will go through, and what information you collect from them; therefore, youâre in full control of the sign-in experience.\r\n\r\nâTap to sign inâ is just the beginning\r\n\r\nDepending on your account configuration, these are the sign-in steps. If you disable any of the following features, your sign-in flow will just skip to the next on the list.\r\n\r\n<strong>Welcome screen</strong>\r\n\r\nUse your iPad to show off your branding: display your logo, a welcome message, full screen slideshow images or any combination of these options. Learn how to get the perfect welcome screen design.\r\n\r\nSign-in fields\r\n\r\nYouâll collect information from visitors on the sign-in field screen. These fields are fully customizable, meaning you can add new fields and edit them as needed. Learn more about customizing the sign-in fields.\r\n\r\n<strong>A couple things to note:</strong>\r\n\r\nHost field: this field appears if you choose to send host notifications. Visitors begin typing their hostâs name, matching options appear on the iPad and the visitor selects their host. Then, Envoy sends a notification (email, SMS, Slack, HipChat) to the employee, letting them know their visitor has arrived.\r\nPurpose of visit field: this optional field will allow you to show different NDAs to visitors based on their purpose of visit.\r\n<strong>NDA</strong>\r\n\r\nVisitors will sign your NDA directly on the iPad, meaning you can cut out the hassle that comes with hard copies. Enable one of our file sharing integrations like Box, Dropbox or Egnyte, to make file storage and sharing even easier. Learn more about customizing the NDA text.\r\n\r\n<strong>Visitor photos</strong>\r\n\r\nThe iPadâs front-facing camera can snap a photo of your visitors. Having photos on file can help ensure office security. Plus, visitor photos appear in host notifications, making it easy for employees to recognize first time visitors. Learn how to enable or disable visitor photos.\r\n\r\n<strong>Final message</strong>\r\n\r\nAdd custom text, an image or play a video as the final sign-in step. Utilize this feature to boost your brand presence with a marketing or recruiting video, or show an evacuation map or safety video to ensure all visitors see required information. Learn more about customizing the final message.', 'How do visitors sign in using Envoy?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'how-do-visitors-sign-in-using-envoy', '', '', '2016-12-18 18:25:59', '2016-12-18 18:25:59', '', 0, 'http://chameleoninfosoft.com/helpdesk/?post_type=help_articles&#038;p=123', 0, 'help_articles', '', 0),
(124, 1, '2016-12-18 18:28:19', '2016-12-18 18:28:19', 'To use Envoy, you just need an iPad, but we also recommend using an iPad stand (like the ones below) to make it easier on visitors.\r\n\r\nTo print visitor badges youâll need the Brother QL-720NW printer (pictured below) and badges. These items can be purchased from the Envoy store or the retailer of your choice.', 'What hardware do I need to use Envoy?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'what-hardware-do-i-need-to-use-envoy', '', '', '2016-12-18 18:28:19', '2016-12-18 18:28:19', '', 0, 'http://chameleoninfosoft.com/helpdesk/?post_type=help_articles&#038;p=124', 0, 'help_articles', '', 0),
(125, 1, '2016-12-18 18:29:30', '2016-12-18 18:29:30', 'We do!\r\n\r\n<strong>Our Envoy Visitor Registration product video</strong>\r\n\r\nThis video highlights what itâs like to sign in as a visitor, as well as demonstrates a few of our most-loved features, as told by our customers.\r\n<strong>Visitor sign-in video demo</strong>\r\n\r\nWatch this video to see what the visitor experience is like.\r\n<strong>Behind the scenes administrator demo</strong>\r\n\r\nWatch this video to learn more about the Envoy dashboard, configuring settings, and more.\r\n<strong>Want even more?</strong>\r\n\r\nYou can find all of our videos, including more demos on specific features, on our YouTube channel.', 'Do you have any video demos of how Envoy works?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'do-you-have-any-video-demos-of-how-envoy-works', '', '', '2016-12-18 18:29:30', '2016-12-18 18:29:30', '', 0, 'http://chameleoninfosoft.com/helpdesk/?post_type=help_articles&#038;p=125', 0, 'help_articles', '', 0),
(126, 1, '2016-12-18 18:34:09', '2016-12-18 18:34:09', 'Itâs very easy to get setup with Envoy. It takes about five minutes on average, especially if you already have an iPad. When it comes to hardware, all youâll need is an iPad (generation 3 or newer) running iOS 8.0 or later.\r\n\r\nGetting started with Envoy video\r\n\r\nThis quick video walks you through the entire onboarding process.\r\nSteps to get started with Envoy\r\n\r\n<strong>1. Sign up for an Envoy account</strong>\r\n\r\nOn your computer, visit our pricing page and choose your plan. Our paid plans come with a 14-day free trial.\r\n\r\n<strong>2. Complete the in-app onboarding steps</strong>\r\n\r\nStill on your computer, youâll walk through the main steps it takes to configure your Envoy account.\r\n\r\n<strong>3. Download the Envoy iPad app</strong>\r\n\r\nNow itâs time to grab your iPad. Open the App Store. Search for âEnvoyâ and download our app.\r\n\r\n<strong>4. Pair your iPad to your Envoy account</strong>\r\n\r\nOpen the Envoy app on your iPad. Click âI have an Envoy accountâ and follow the instructions to pair your device.\r\n\r\n<strong>5. Sign yourself in as a test visitor!</strong>\r\n\r\nWhen your logo appears on the iPad, sign yourself in as a test visitor. Just tap the âtap to sign inâ button and sign in. Then, visit your Envoy dashboard to see your sign-in.', 'How easy is it to get set up?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'how-easy-is-it-to-get-set-up', '', '', '2016-12-18 18:34:09', '2016-12-18 18:34:09', '', 0, 'http://chameleoninfosoft.com/helpdesk/?post_type=help_articles&#038;p=126', 0, 'help_articles', '', 0),
(127, 1, '2016-12-18 18:39:13', '2016-12-18 18:39:13', 'Absolutely. Weâre proud that some of the biggest names in the world choose and trust Envoy. You can check out some of our customer stories below:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>MailChimp</li>\r\n 	<li>Asana</li>\r\n 	<li>POPSUGAR</li>\r\n 	<li>Headspace</li>\r\n 	<li>Compass</li>\r\n 	<li>AMAG Pharmaceuticals</li>\r\n 	<li>Galvanize (coworking space)</li>\r\n 	<li>OnRamp (data center)</li>\r\n 	<li>USC Credit Union</li>\r\n 	<li>Gateway Church</li>\r\n 	<li>Whitby School</li>\r\n 	<li>LEAD Elementary</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;', 'Do you have any customer stories or case studies I can look at?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'do-you-have-any-customer-stories-or-case-studies-i-can-look-at', '', '', '2016-12-18 18:39:13', '2016-12-18 18:39:13', '', 0, 'http://chameleoninfosoft.com/helpdesk/?post_type=help_articles&#038;p=127', 0, 'help_articles', '', 0),
(128, 1, '2016-12-18 18:39:41', '2016-12-18 18:39:41', 'At Envoy, we understand the sensitivity of your data, and weâre committed to ensuring confidentiality and reliability as critical components of our service to you. We take your trust very seriously, and weâre proud to provide a secure infrastructure that protects your visitor data and company information.\r\n\r\nThousands of global companies choose and trust Envoy, from private companies like Pixar, Reddit and Uber, to public companies such as Yelp, Pandora, Box and Shopify. Plus, customers from highly-regulated industries like OnRamp (data center), Roche (pharmaceutical) and Planet Labs (government) all depend on Envoy to demonstrate compliance.\r\n\r\nFor more details, you can visit our <a href=\"https://envoy.com/security-details/\">security page</a>, which covers topics like centralized account management, infrastructure, data storage and privacy.', 'Where can I learn about your security?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'where-can-i-learn-about-your-security', '', '', '2016-12-18 18:39:41', '2016-12-18 18:39:41', '', 0, 'http://chameleoninfosoft.com/helpdesk/?post_type=help_articles&#038;p=128', 0, 'help_articles', '', 0),
(129, 1, '2016-12-18 18:40:11', '2016-12-18 18:40:11', 'Yes. Envoy is a cloud-based platform. Your directory entries, visitor data and signed agreements are all encrypted and stored on secure servers. This means your data is easily accessible, continually backed up and safe.\r\n\r\nEnvoy can be used anywhere, at any time, so itâs perfect for centrally managing multiple offices from one company account.\r\n\r\nYou can even use Envoy if youâre not connected to Wi-Fi. If your iPad is disconnected from a network connection, visitors can continue to sign in, and their data will be stored locally on the device. Upon reestablishing network connectivity, all locally stored visitor data will sync to Envoy.', 'Is Envoy cloud-based?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'is-envoy-cloud-based', '', '', '2016-12-18 18:40:11', '2016-12-18 18:40:11', '', 0, 'http://chameleoninfosoft.com/helpdesk/?post_type=help_articles&#038;p=129', 0, 'help_articles', '', 0),
(130, 1, '2016-12-18 18:40:41', '2016-12-18 18:40:41', 'Envoy supports 17 languages\r\n\r\nChinese (simplified and traditional)\r\nDanish\r\nDutch\r\nEnglish\r\nFinnish\r\nFrench\r\nGerman\r\nHindi\r\nItalian\r\nJapanese\r\nKorean\r\nNorwegian\r\nPortuguese\r\nRomanian\r\nRussian\r\nSpanish\r\nSwedish\r\nHow do I change the language?\r\n\r\nFollow this guide to change the display language on your iPad.', 'Which languages do you support?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'which-languages-do-you-support', '', '', '2016-12-18 18:40:41', '2016-12-18 18:40:41', '', 0, 'http://chameleoninfosoft.com/helpdesk/?post_type=help_articles&#038;p=130', 0, 'help_articles', '', 0),
(131, 1, '2016-12-18 18:41:29', '2016-12-18 18:41:29', 'For the majority of our customers, a âlocationâ is defined as a physical office location. For example, if a company has several offices all over the world, they would typically set up one Envoy location for each of them. Alternatively, if a company has several buildings within one central campus, they may want to set up an Envoy location for each of those buildings as well. (This is what one of our customers, Gateway Church, does.) This also means that for every location you set up, you would typically need to order the associated hardware, i.e. iPad and badge printer and iPad stand.\r\n\r\nAnother way to think about it\r\n\r\nEach location has its own separate visitor dashboard. This dashboard is the real-time record of whoâs in the building. At a glance, you can easily access any necessary information about a visitor, including what time they signed in or out, who they were visiting and more. It can be easily searched or exported to provide backup in the case of an emergency or compliance audit.\r\n\r\nIf you need to ensure that visitor data from different offices, entrances or buildings doesnât blend together, then itâs best to buy separate locations for all of them.\r\n\r\n<strong>What hardware can be used at one location?</strong>\r\n\r\nOn Basic, Standard and Premium plans, you can pair unlimited iPads per location to help you speed up sign-in. With multiple iPads, multiple visitors can all sign in at the same time. This is helpful if you have large groups of visitors all arriving at once.\r\n\r\nEach iPad will display the same logo, sign-in fields, NDA settings, etc. All of the visitor data collected on all of these iPads will appear on your locationâs dashboard.\r\n\r\nIf youâre using badge printing on a Standard or Premium plan, you can use one badge printer per location. Even if youâre using multiple iPads, all visitor badges will print from one printer.\r\n\r\nIf you need to use multiple printers at your location, please contact us.', 'I see that you charge per location. How do you define a location?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'i-see-that-you-charge-per-location-how-do-you-define-a-location', '', '', '2016-12-18 18:41:29', '2016-12-18 18:41:29', '', 0, 'http://chameleoninfosoft.com/helpdesk/?post_type=help_articles&#038;p=131', 0, 'help_articles', '', 0),
(132, 1, '2016-12-18 18:42:03', '2016-12-18 18:42:03', 'Of course! You can explore all of Envoyâs features with a 14-day free trial before deciding if youâd like to purchase.\r\n\r\nYou can review our plans and sign up for a trial on our pricing page.', 'Can I try out Envoy for free before purchasing it?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'can-i-try-out-envoy-for-free-before-purchasing-it', '', '', '2016-12-18 18:42:03', '2016-12-18 18:42:03', '', 0, 'http://chameleoninfosoft.com/helpdesk/?post_type=help_articles&#038;p=132', 0, 'help_articles', '', 0),
(133, 1, '2016-12-18 18:42:35', '2016-12-18 18:42:35', 'If you need to extend your trial for a few more days to explore the system further, weâre happy to help. Just contact us and let us know how we can help.', 'Can I extend my trial?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'can-i-extend-my-trial', '', '', '2016-12-18 18:42:35', '2016-12-18 18:42:35', '', 0, 'http://chameleoninfosoft.com/helpdesk/?post_type=help_articles&#038;p=133', 0, 'help_articles', '', 0),
(134, 1, '2016-12-18 18:43:06', '2016-12-18 18:43:06', 'You can learn about all the different plans we offer in detail on our pricing page. to get the basics, we recommend you read on below.\r\n\r\nWeâve also developed an interactive guide to help guide to you to the right plan based on your specific needs. Check it out here!\r\n\r\nBasic Plan\r\n\r\nWe recommend this plan if youâre a small company with only one location, fewer than 50 employees and a small number of visitors. On the Basic Plan, youâll get all of the following functionality:\r\n\r\nVisitors: unlimited\r\niPads: unlimited\r\nEmployee hosts: up to 50\r\nCustomizations: logo and brand color, sign-in fields and final message\r\nHost notifications: email and push notification (via Envoy Passport mobile app)\r\nBadge printing: not available on Basic Plan\r\nNDA signing: not available on Basic Plan\r\nPre-registration\r\nIntegrations: Zapier, IFTTT, Eventbrite\r\nSupport: basic support\r\nStandard Plan\r\n\r\nWe recommend this plan if youâre a growing company with more than 50 employees, or two locations or more. This is also a perfect plan if youâre looking for a robust system that factors in confidentiality and security concerns. On the Standard Plan, youâll get all of the following functionality:\r\n\r\nVisitors: unlimited\r\niPads: unlimited\r\nEmployee hosts: unlimited\r\nCustomizations: logo and brand color, sign-in fields and final message\r\nHost notifications: email, Slack, HipChat, Office 365 Groups and push notification (via Envoy Passport mobile app)\r\nBadge printing\r\nNDA signing\r\nPre-registration\r\nIntegrations: Slack, HipChat, Office 365 Groups, Zapier, IFTTT, Eventbrite\r\nSupport: standard support\r\nPremium Plan\r\n\r\nWe recommend this plan if youâre an established company with several locations thatâs looking for a complete, integrated visitor experience. On the Premium Plan, youâll get all of the following functionality:\r\n\r\nVisitors: unlimited\r\niPads: unlimited\r\nEmployee hosts: unlimited\r\nCustomizations: logo and brand color, sign-in fields and final message\r\nHost notifications: email, Slack, HipChat, Office 365 Groups and push notification (via Envoy Passport mobile app)\r\nBadge printing, custom badges and custom badge CSS\r\nNDA signing\r\nPre-registration\r\nIntegrations: Active Directory, Google Apps for Work, Okta, Onelogin, Box, Dropbox, Egnyte, Salesforce, MailChimp Slack, HipChat, Office 365 Groups, Zapier, IFTTT, Eventbrite\r\nSupport: premium support\r\nEnterprise Plan\r\n\r\nWe recommend this plan if youâre an enterprise company with multiple locations across the globe. Enterprise customers get everything from the Premium Plan, plus the special white-glove features below:\r\n\r\nSLA &amp; custom Terms of Service\r\nDedicated Account Manager\r\nOne free iPad, badge printer and iPad stand per location\r\nIntegrations: Avigilon, Aruba ClearPass, Active Directory, Google Apps for Work, Okta, Onelogin, Box, Dropbox, Egnyte, Salesforce, MailChimp Slack, HipChat, Office 365 Groups, Zapier, IFTTT, Eventbrite\r\nSupport: priority, enterprise support', 'Which plan should our company choose?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'which-plan-should-our-company-choose', '', '', '2016-12-18 18:43:06', '2016-12-18 18:43:06', '', 0, 'http://chameleoninfosoft.com/helpdesk/?post_type=help_articles&#038;p=134', 0, 'help_articles', '', 0),
(135, 1, '2016-12-18 18:43:54', '2016-12-18 18:43:54', 'We do offer special discounts for academic institutions or nonprofits. Please contact us to learn more.', 'Do you have special pricing for academic institutions or nonprofits?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'do-you-have-special-pricing-for-academic-institutions-or-nonprofits', '', '', '2016-12-18 18:43:54', '2016-12-18 18:43:54', '', 0, 'http://chameleoninfosoft.com/helpdesk/?post_type=help_articles&#038;p=135', 0, 'help_articles', '', 0),
(136, 1, '2016-12-18 18:44:28', '2016-12-18 18:44:28', 'At Envoy, we believe that connecting with customer support should never be a chore. Weâre the highest-rated visitor registration product on top review sites, including Capterra, GetApp and G2 Crowd, and if you read our reviews, youâll notice that many of our customers rank our support team as one of their favorite things about us. We also wrote a post about our unique approach to support, as well as our customer support âmantras.â\r\n\r\n<strong>How to reach us</strong>\r\n\r\nContact us or email us at hi@envoy.com\r\nLive chat with us from 7 am to 5 pm PT. Just click on the chat button in the bottom right corner of this browser.', 'What kind of customer support do you offer?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'what-kind-of-customer-support-do-you-offer', '', '', '2016-12-18 18:44:28', '2016-12-18 18:44:28', '', 0, 'http://chameleoninfosoft.com/helpdesk/?post_type=help_articles&#038;p=136', 0, 'help_articles', '', 0),
(137, 1, '2016-12-18 18:45:46', '2016-12-18 18:45:46', '<strong>Envoy can be used anywhere</strong>\r\n\r\nWeâre currently being used in 57 different countries, however, you can use Envoy literally anywhere as long as you have an iPad, a computer and an Internet connection! Weâre also available in 17 different languages (you can find the full list here.)\r\n\r\nNote: Learn more about known SMS issues in China and India.\r\n\r\n<strong>Purchasing hardware</strong>\r\n\r\nYou can purchase hardware separately or through our online store. We can currently ship iPads and printers only to the USA, Canada and Mexico (due to plug and socket compatibility).\r\n\r\nIf youâre outside the USA, Canada or Mexico, we recommend you purchase the following items from the retailer of your choice:\r\n\r\niPad (any model iPad 3 or newer)\r\nBrother QL-720NW printer\r\nWe do ship iPad stands, plain badges and custom badges internationally.', 'What countries is Envoy available in? Can we purchase your hardware internationally?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'what-countries-is-envoy-available-in-can-we-purchase-your-hardware-internationally', '', '', '2016-12-18 18:45:46', '2016-12-18 18:45:46', '', 0, 'http://chameleoninfosoft.com/helpdesk/?post_type=help_articles&#038;p=137', 0, 'help_articles', '', 0),
(138, 1, '2016-12-18 18:46:07', '2016-12-18 18:46:07', 'Depending on the scope of the integration, we are definitely willing to work with customers on this. You can reach out to our sales team via our contact form for more information.', 'Do you offer custom integrations?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'do-you-offer-custom-integrations', '', '', '2016-12-18 18:46:07', '2016-12-18 18:46:07', '', 0, 'http://chameleoninfosoft.com/helpdesk/?post_type=help_articles&#038;p=138', 0, 'help_articles', '', 0),
(139, 1, '2016-12-18 18:46:30', '2016-12-18 18:46:30', 'Absolutely. Here is a list of material that our customers have found very helpful in learning about Envoy:\r\n\r\nCase studies: Read stories of how customers like MailChimp, POPSUGAR and Asana use Envoy.\r\nOne-page PDF: Learn about Envoyâs key features and benefits.\r\nVideo demos: See what itâs like to sign in with Envoy or use Envoy as an admin.\r\nOur blog: Check out highlights different product features, use cases and customer stories\r\nIf youâre interested in reading more about what our customers have to say, you can check out our reviews on sites like Capterra, GetApp and G2 Crowd. You can also check out the nice things our customers say about us on Twitter.', 'Do you have any materials about Envoy that I can show the rest of my team?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'do-you-have-any-materials-about-envoy-that-i-can-show-the-rest-of-my-team', '', '', '2016-12-18 18:46:30', '2016-12-18 18:46:30', '', 0, 'http://chameleoninfosoft.com/helpdesk/?post_type=help_articles&#038;p=139', 0, 'help_articles', '', 0),
(140, 1, '2016-12-18 18:47:11', '2016-12-18 18:47:11', 'All customer data and metadata is stored in AWS (Amazon Web Services) in the US-East-1 DC data center in Virginia. Envoy never stores customer data on local devices or any other internal network.', 'Where is customer data stored?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'where-is-customer-data-stored', '', '', '2016-12-18 18:47:11', '2016-12-18 18:47:11', '', 0, 'http://chameleoninfosoft.com/helpdesk/?post_type=help_articles&#038;p=140', 0, 'help_articles', '', 0),
(141, 1, '2016-12-18 18:48:34', '2016-12-18 18:48:34', 'Our support team only accesses customer accounts in the event of a technical support issues that requires real-time access. Envoy forbids accessing client data outside of those circumstances.\r\n\r\nRead our full privacy policy for more details.', 'Who can access customer data?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'who-can-access-customer-data', '', '', '2016-12-18 18:48:34', '2016-12-18 18:48:34', '', 0, 'http://chameleoninfosoft.com/helpdesk/?post_type=help_articles&#038;p=141', 0, 'help_articles', '', 0),
(142, 1, '2016-12-18 18:50:24', '2016-12-18 18:50:24', 'End users may authenticate to Envoy either with a username and password or by enabling SAML-based single sign-on. Envoy supports SAML 2.0 and can integrate with most IdPs, including Okta and ADFS.', 'How do Envoy users authenticate to the dashboard?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'how-do-envoy-users-authenticate-to-the-dashboard', '', '', '2016-12-18 18:50:24', '2016-12-18 18:50:24', '', 0, 'http://chameleoninfosoft.com/helpdesk/?post_type=help_articles&#038;p=142', 0, 'help_articles', '', 0),
(143, 1, '2016-12-18 18:50:46', '2016-12-18 18:50:46', 'Envoy uses Heroku Encrypted Postgres (AES-256 disk encryption). Private TLS keys are managed by Cloudflare; disk encryption keys for data at rest are managed by Heroku and AWS; application encryption keys are managed by Heroku with restricted access for required Envoy employees.', 'How does Envoy manage data encryption?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'how-does-envoy-manage-data-encryption', '', '', '2016-12-18 18:50:46', '2016-12-18 18:50:46', '', 0, 'http://chameleoninfosoft.com/helpdesk/?post_type=help_articles&#038;p=143', 0, 'help_articles', '', 0),
(144, 1, '2016-12-18 18:51:06', '2016-12-18 18:51:06', 'We offer flexible pricing, including monthly and yearly plans. With our monthly plans, youâre subscribed on a month-to-month basis, and you can cancel at any time. If you decide to cancel your yearly plan, weâll be happy to refund you for the remaining period.', 'What is your cancellation policy?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'what-is-your-cancellation-policy', '', '', '2016-12-18 18:51:06', '2016-12-18 18:51:06', '', 0, 'http://chameleoninfosoft.com/helpdesk/?post_type=help_articles&#038;p=144', 0, 'help_articles', '', 0),
(145, 1, '2016-12-18 18:51:28', '2016-12-18 18:51:28', 'We offer invoiced billing for Premium accounts with three or more locations. For more information, you can contact our sales team.', 'Do you offer invoiced billing?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'do-you-offer-invoiced-billing', '', '', '2016-12-18 18:51:28', '2016-12-18 18:51:28', '', 0, 'http://chameleoninfosoft.com/helpdesk/?post_type=help_articles&#038;p=145', 0, 'help_articles', '', 0),
(146, 1, '2016-12-18 18:52:02', '2016-12-18 18:52:02', 'Standard Plan\r\n\r\nWe do not currently supply formal quotes for our Standard plan, but you can find all of the pricing and details on our pricing page.\r\n\r\nPremium or Enterprise Plan\r\n\r\nIf you need an official quote for our Premium or Enterprise plan, you can send a request to our sales team. We will typically return your email within 24 hours (on normal business days.) Here are the instructions:\r\n\r\nGo to our contact form.\r\nUnder âQuestion Type,â select âSales.â\r\nEnter in your first name, last name, email and company name.\r\nIn the message field, please specify the following:\r\nWhich plan youâre interested in\r\nWhether youâd like to pay monthly or yearly\r\nThe number of locations', 'How can I request a formal quote?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'how-can-i-request-a-formal-quote', '', '', '2016-12-18 18:52:02', '2016-12-18 18:52:02', '', 0, 'http://chameleoninfosoft.com/helpdesk/?post_type=help_articles&#038;p=146', 0, 'help_articles', '', 0),
(147, 1, '2016-12-18 18:52:22', '2016-12-18 18:52:22', 'No, there are no taxes applied on top of the subscription charge.', 'Are there any applicable taxes?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'are-there-any-applicable-taxes', '', '', '2016-12-18 18:52:22', '2016-12-18 18:52:22', '', 0, 'http://chameleoninfosoft.com/helpdesk/?post_type=help_articles&#038;p=147', 0, 'help_articles', '', 0),
(148, 1, '2016-12-18 18:52:43', '2016-12-18 18:52:43', 'For online transactions, we currently accept any credit or debit card with Mastercard, Visa, Discover Network, American Express.\r\n\r\nFor manual invoicing (which requires the Enterprise Plan or three or more Premium locations), we accept payment via ACH or check.', 'What forms of payment do you accept?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'what-forms-of-payment-do-you-accept', '', '', '2016-12-18 18:52:43', '2016-12-18 18:52:43', '', 0, 'http://chameleoninfosoft.com/helpdesk/?post_type=help_articles&#038;p=148', 0, 'help_articles', '', 0),
(149, 1, '2016-12-18 18:53:03', '2016-12-18 18:53:03', 'We hate hidden fees as much as you do. If youâre on the monthly plan, youâll be charged once a month on your renewal date. If youâre on the yearly plan, we only charge up one fee up front for the whole month, and your card will not be charged until your renewal date on the following year. Thatâs it!', 'Are there any hidden fees?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'are-there-any-hidden-fees', '', '', '2016-12-18 18:53:03', '2016-12-18 18:53:03', '', 0, 'http://chameleoninfosoft.com/helpdesk/?post_type=help_articles&#038;p=149', 0, 'help_articles', '', 0),
